; MCPd-Watchdog - relaunch MCPd if it exits.
;
; Invoked from S:Network-Startup as:
;     Run >NIL: <NIL: Execute SYS:System/MCPd/MCPd-Watchdog
;
; Each iteration runs MCPd synchronously. If MCPd exits (clean Break
; or crash), we wait 5s and relaunch. The Wait gives a fast-fail
; startup loop a chance to be interrupted via Break, and stops it
; from burning CPU.
;
; Logs to T:MCPd-Watchdog.log (RAM-backed, wiped on reboot).
;
; To stop the watchdog: Break the process (Status FULL to find pid,
; then Break <pid> C). The Break interrupts the Wait or the running
; MCPd, the script exits cleanly.

FailAt 99999

Echo >>T:MCPd-Watchdog.log "==== watchdog starting ===="

Lab loop
    Echo >>T:MCPd-Watchdog.log "[*] launching MCPd"
    SYS:System/MCPd/MCPd
    Echo >>T:MCPd-Watchdog.log "[*] MCPd exited rc=$RC; sleeping 5s"
    Wait 5
Skip loop BACK
